  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Ambulance Incident - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_ambulance_incident">Ambulance Incident</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_contact">CARE CONTACT</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_ambulance_incident">Ambulance Incident</xref>
 is a call to the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_ambulance_control_room">Ambulance Control Room</xref>
 that, following initial triage, requires a face to face response from the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_ambulance_service">Ambulance Service</xref>
 or can be resolved with telephone advice and any appropriate actions agreed with the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
For further information on 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_ambulance_incident">Ambulance Incidents</xref>
, see the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nhs_england">NHS England</xref>
 website at: 
    <xref href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/ambulance-quality-indicators/"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Ambulance Quality Indicators</xref>
.  </p>

